  "informal_statement": "For all reals a, b, c, d: max (a+b) (c+d) <= max a c + max b d -- the maximum function is subadditive.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "By max_le, it suffices to show both a+b and c+d are at most max a c + max b d. The first follows from le_max_left a c (a <= max a c) and le_max_left b d (b <= max b d), summed via linarith; the second follows symmetrically from le_max_right on both pairs.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem max_add_le (a b c d : ℝ) : max (a + b) (c + d) ≤ max a c + max b d",
